==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexperience
<hw>In`ex*pe"ri*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexperientia</ets>, cf. F. <ets>inexp⟦eacute⟧rience</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Experience</er>.]</ety> <def>Absence or lack
of experience; lack of personal and experimental knowledge; <as>as, the
<ex>inexperience</ex> of youth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Failings which are incident to youth and
<qex>inexperience</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prejudice and self-sufficiency naturally proceed from
<qex>inexperience</qex> of the world, and ignorance of mankind.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexperienced</ent>⟦br⟧
